{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the model trained with labels provided by different experts -as it is here -provides an approach to assess the consistency of labels quantitatively across experts and categories, which can be used to assess and resolve inconsistencies in other datasets or implementations.",
    "Zhong et al. (2017) compare the efficacy of diverse CNN architectures like VGG16, ResNet50, and their hybrid CNN for Foraminifera classification.",
    "They compared the models with ML techniques fed with features extracted from VGG16 models.",
    "The training dataset had images of only one orientation under different lighting, compromising model generalizability on more extensive, diverse testing data.",
    "Lastly, Pires de Lima et al. (2020) present five standard DL networks (VGG19, InceptionV3, MobileNetV2, ResNet50, and DenseNet121) fine-tuned for the classification of late Paleozoic fusulinids through 2D thin-section images."
  ]
}